<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-01T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-01T05:00:00-05:00" n="752" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/47<hi rend="superscript">16/22</hi>: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">La Bourboule</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-01T12:00:00+02:00">July
                                        1, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received July 2—9:15
                                    a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4. Telegram No. 380, June 28, 8 p.m. to Consul Bordeaux, repeated
                                here. I took this question of our wolframite and antimony up with
                                    <pb facs="0660" n="651" xml:id="pg_651"/> Charveriat<note n="27" xml:id="d752fn27">Emile Charveriat, Director of Political and
                                    Commercial Affairs in the French Foreign Office.</note> this
                                morning. He is sending instructions immediately to authorize release
                                of these ores.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>